73
0:04:00.16,000 --> 0:04:04,000
It's not realistic with lifelong treatment

74
0:04:04.16,000 --> 0:04:06,000
for everyone in the poorest countries.

75
0:04:06.16,000 --> 0:04:09,000
But it's very good that what is done is being done.

76
0:04:09.16,000 --> 0:04:13,000
But focus now is back on prevention.

77
0:04:13.16,000 --> 0:04:16,000
It is only by stopping the transmission

78
0:04:16.16,000 --> 0:04:19,000
that the world will be able to deal with it.

79
0:04:19.16,000 --> 0:04:21,000
Drugs is too costly -- had we had the vaccine,

80
0:04:21.16,000 --> 0:04:24,000
or when we will get the vaccine, that's something more effective --

81
0:04:24.16,000 --> 0:04:26,000
but the drugs are very costly for the poor.

82
0:04:26.16,000 --> 0:04:28,000
Not the drug in itself, but the treatment

83
0:04:28.16,000 --> 0:04:3,000
and the care which is needed around it.

84
0:04:32.16,000 --> 0:04:35,000
So, when we look at the pattern,

85
0:04:35.16,000 --> 0:04:37,000
one thing comes out very clearly:

86
0:04:37.16,000 --> 0:04:39,000
you see the blue bubbles

87
0:04:39.16,000 --> 0:04:41,000
and people say HIV is very high in Africa.

88
0:04:41.16,000 --> 0:04:44,000
I would say, HIV is very different in Africa.

89
0:04:44.16,000 --> 0:04:48,000
You'll find the highest HIV rate in the world

90
0:04:48.16,000 --> 0:04:5,000
in African countries,

91
0:04:50.16,000 --> 0:04:52,000
and yet you'll find Senegal, down here --

92
