103
0:05:21.16,000 --> 0:05:25,000
I found out that Salt Lake City and San Francisco were different.

104
0:05:25.16,000 --> 0:05:27,000
(Laughter)

105
0:05:27.16,000 --> 0:05:3,000
And so it is in Africa -- it's a lot of difference.

106
0:05:30.16,000 --> 0:05:32,000
So, why is it so high? Is it war?

107
0:05:32.16,000 --> 0:05:34,000
No, it's not. Look here.

108
0:05:34.16,000 --> 0:05:37,000
War-torn Congo is down there -- two, three, four percent.

109
0:05:37.16,000 --> 0:05:41,000
And this is peaceful Zambia, neighboring country -- 15 percent.

110
0:05:41.16,000 --> 0:05:44,000
And there's good studies of the refugees coming out of Congo --

111
0:05:44.16,000 --> 0:05:46,000
they have two, three percent infected,

112
0:05:46.16,000 --> 0:05:48,000
and peaceful Zambia -- much higher.

113
0:05:48.16,000 --> 0:05:5,000
There are now studies clearly showing

114
0:05:50.16,000 --> 0:05:53,000
that the wars are terrible, that rapes are terrible,

115
0:05:53.16,000 --> 0:05:56,000
but this is not the driving force for the high levels in Africa.

116
0:05:56.16,000 --> 0:05:58,000
So, is it poverty?

117
0:05:58.16,000 --> 0:06:,000
Well if you look at the macro level,

118
0:06:00.16,000 --> 0:06:02,000
it seems more money, more HIV.

119
0:06:02.16,000 --> 0:06:05,000
But that's very simplistic,

120
0:06:05.16,000 --> 0:06:07,000
so let's go down and look at Tanzania.

121
0:06:07.16,000 --> 0:06:11,000
I will split Tanzania in five income groups,

122
0:06:11.16,000 --> 0:06:13,000
from the highest income to the lowest income,

123
0:06:13.16,000 --> 0:06:15,000
and here we go.

124
0:06:15.16,000 --> 0:06:18,000
The ones with the highest income, the better off -- I wouldn't say rich --

125
0:06:18.16,000 --> 0:06:2,000
they have higher HIV.

126
0:06:20.16,000 --> 0:06:23,000
The difference goes from 11 percent down to four percent,

127
0:06:23.16,000 --> 0:06:25,000
and it is even bigger among women.

128
0:06:25.16,000 --> 0:06:29,000
There's a lot of things that we thought, that now, good research,

129
0:06:29.16,000 --> 0:06:32,000
done by African institutions and researchers

130
0:06:32.16,000 --> 0:06:35,000
together with the international researchers, show that that's not the case.

131
0:06:35.16,000 --> 0:06:37,000
So, this is the difference within Tanzania.

132
0:06:37.16,000 --> 0:06:39,000
And, I can't avoid showing Kenya.

133
0:06:39.16,000 --> 0:06:41,000
Look here at Kenya.

134
0:06:41.16,000 --> 0:06:43,000
I've split Kenya in its provinces.

135
0:06:43.16,000 --> 0:06:45,000
Here it goes.

136
0:06:45.16,000 --> 0:06:48,000
See the difference within one African country --

137
0:06:48.16,000 --> 0:06:51,000
it goes from very low level to very high level,

138
0:06:51.16,000 --> 0:06:54,000
and most of the provinces in Kenya is quite modest.

139
0:06:54.16,000 --> 0:06:56,000
So, what is it then?

140
0:06:56.16,000 --> 0:07:,000
Why do we see this extremely high levels in some countries?

141
0:07:00.16,000 --> 0:07:03,000
Well, it is more common with multiple partners,

142
0:07:03.16,000 --> 0:07:06,000
there is less condom use,

143
0:07:06.16,000 --> 0:07:09,000
and there is age-disparate sex --

144
0:07:09.16,000 --> 0:07:12,000
that is, older men tend to have sex with younger women.

145
0:07:12.16,000 --> 0:07:15,000
We see higher rates in younger women than younger men

146
0:07:15.16,000 --> 0:07:17,000
in many of these highly affected countries.

147
0:07:17.16,000 --> 0:07:19,000
But where are they situated?

148
0:07:19.16,000 --> 0:07:21,000
I will swap the bubbles to a map.

149
0:07:21.16,000 --> 0:07:25,000
Look, the highly infected are four percent of all population

150
0:07:25.16,000 --> 0:07:28,000
and they hold 50 percent of the HIV-infected.

151
0:07:28.16,000 --> 0:07:31,000
HIV exists all over the world.

152
0:07:31.16,000 --> 0:07:33,000
Look, you have bubbles all over the world here.

153
0:07:33.16,000 --> 0:07:36,000
Brazil has many HIV-infected.

154
0:07:36.16,000 --> 0:07:39,000
Arab countries not so much, but Iran is quite high.

155
0:07:39.16,000 --> 0:07:43,000
They have heroin addiction and also prostitution in Iran.

156
0:07:43.16,000 --> 0:07:45,000
India has many because they are many.

157
0:07:45.16,000 --> 0:07:47,000
Southeast Asia, and so on.

158
0:07:47.16,000 --> 0:07:49,000
But, there is one part of Africa --

159
0:07:49.16,000 --> 0:07:51,000
and the difficult thing is, at the same time,

160
0:07:51.16,000 --> 0:07:55,000
not to make a uniform statement about Africa,

161
0:07:55.16,000 --> 0:07:59,000
not to come to simple ideas of why it is like this, on one hand.

162
0:07:59.16,000 --> 0:08:02,000
On the other hand, try to say that this is not the case,

163
0:08:02.16,000 --> 0:08:06,000
because there is a scientific consensus about this pattern now.

164
0:08:06.16,000 --> 0:08:09,000
UNAIDS have done good data available, finally,

165
0:08:09.16,000 --> 0:08:12,000
about the spread of HIV.

166
0:08:12.16,000 --> 0:08:15,000
It could be concurrency.

167
0:08:15.16,000 --> 0:08:18,000
It could be some virus types.

168
0:08:18.16,000 --> 0:08:22,000
It could be that there is other things

169
0:08:22.16,000 --> 0:08:25,000
which makes transmission occur in a higher frequency.

170
0:08:25.16,000 --> 0:08:28,000
After all, if you are completely healthy and you have heterosexual sex,

171
0:08:28.16,000 --> 0:08:33,000
the risk of infection in one intercourse is one in 1,000.

172
0:08:33.16,000 --> 0:08:35,000
Don't jump to conclusions now on how to

173
0:08:35.16,000 --> 0:08:37,000
behave tonight and so on.

174
0:08:37.16,000 --> 0:08:39,000
(Laughter)

175
0:08:39.16,000 --> 0:08:42,000
But -- and if you are in an unfavorable situation,

176
0:08:42.16,000 --> 0:08:45,000
more sexually transmitted diseases, it can be one in 100.

177
0:08:45.16,000 --> 0:08:48,000
But what we think is that it could be concurrency.

178
0:08:48.16,000 --> 0:08:5,000
And what is concurrency?

179
0:08:50.16,000 --> 0:08:52,000
In Sweden, we have no concurrency.

180
0:08:52.16,000 --> 0:08:54,000
